snippet: The United States is shut out of the late rounds at Wimbledon, but Canada will send Milos Raonic into the men’s semifinals Friday and Eugenie Bouchard into the women’s final Saturday.
abstract: Harvey Araton On Tennis column examines Canada's unexpected emergence into limelight of professional tennis; observes that country that has always regarded the sport as an afterthought is now preparing to send Milos Raonic into men's semifinals and Eugenie Bouchard into women's final at Wimbledon.
lead_paragraph: The United States is shut out of the late rounds at Wimbledon, but Canada will send Milos Raonic into the men’s semifinals Friday and Eugenie Bouchard into the women’s final Saturday.

headline.seo: Wimbledon 2014: Home of Raonic and Bouchard, Canada Has Made Great Strides
headline.main: For Inspiration, the United States Should Probably Look North
headline.print_headline: For Inspiration, the United States Should Probably Look North
